In [10]:
# array to store areas
area_tot = []

# loop through the images
for f in im_names:
    
    # read in the file
    im = skimage.io.imread(f)
    
    # normalize the image
    im_norm = (im - im.min()) / (im.max() - im.min())
    
    # threshold
    im_thresh = im_norm > 0.4
    
    # update area array
    area_tot.append(np.sum(im_thresh))
In [11]:
times = np.arange(len(im_names))*5
plt.plot(times, area_tot, '.')
plt.ylabel("pixel area")
plt.xlabel("time (mins)")
plt.yscale("linear")

N0 = area_tot[0]
areas1 = N0 * np.exp(0.015*times)
areas2 = N0 * np.exp(0.02*times)
areas3 = N0 * np.exp(0.025*times)

plt.plot(times, areas1)
plt.plot(times, areas2)
plt.plot(times, areas3)
plt.yscale("log")

plt.legend(["data", "k=0.015", "k=0.02", "k=0.025"])

In [12]:
ks = np.linspace(0.01, 0.03, 100)
chi_squares = np.zeros(len(ks))

# i is our counter
# k is our growth rate values
for i, k in enumerate(ks):
 
    theory_curve = N0 * np.exp(k*times)
    chi_square = np.sum((area_tot - theory_curve)**2)
    chi_squares[i] = chi_square
